words.definition: If something is analogous to something else, it is similar in some way.
words.example: The wings of a bird are analogous to the arms of a human.

words.definition: Binoculars are a device used for seeing things that are far away.
words.example: He used his binoculars to watch the birds in the trees.

words.definition: The bulk of something is its large size or the main part of it.
words.example: The bulk of the work has already been completed.

words.definition: To comprise something means to consist of or be made up of it.
words.example: The team comprises players from many different countries.

words.definition: To depict something means to show it in a drawing or painting.
words.example: The painting depicts a scene from a famous battle.

words.definition: If something is dual, it has two parts or functions.
words.example: The car has a dual exhaust system.

words.definition: Fahrenheit is a scale for measuring temperature.
words.example: Water freezes at 32 degrees Fahrenheit.

words.definition: To fulfill something means to achieve or complete it.
words.example: He finally fulfilled his dream of becoming a pilot.

words.definition: A grove is a small group of trees.
words.example: The picnic was held in a quiet orange grove.

words.definition: Ore is rock from which metal can be extracted.
words.example: The miners extracted iron ore from the ground.

words.definition: The outback is the remote and dry area in the middle of Australia.
words.example: Many unique animals live in the Australian outback.

words.definition: To outweigh something means to be more important or significant than it.
words.example: The benefits of the new plan outweigh the costs.

words.definition: A paradox is a situation that seems impossible because it has opposite qualities.
words.example: It is a paradox that such a wealthy country has so many poor people.

words.definition: A pier is a structure that goes out into the water for people to walk on or for boats to tie to.
words.example: We walked along the pier to watch the sunset.

words.definition: A shortcut is a quicker way to get somewhere.
words.example: We took a shortcut through the park to get home faster.

words.definition: A tariff is a tax that is paid on goods coming into a country.
words.example: The government imposed a new tariff on imported electronics.

words.definition: A thermometer is a device used for measuring temperature.
words.example: The thermometer showed that the temperature was 25 degrees.

words.definition: To tilt something means to move it so that one side is higher than the other.
words.example: He tilted his head to the side as he listened to the music.

words.definition: Vice versa means that the opposite of what has been said is also true.
words.example: She dislikes him, and vice versa.

words.definition: A person's whereabouts is the place where they are.
words.example: The police are still trying to determine the suspect's whereabouts.
